1
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:19,477
Power to The People

2
00:00:19,478 --> 00:00:24,733
With my mighty arm
I'll bring this to an end

3
00:00:29,488 --> 00:00:33,282
It's my Turn!

4
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,409
Here we go again

5
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:37,578
We swarm the Association as a pack!

6
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:38,704
Dangerous to the max

7
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:40,248
Already at the limit

8
00:00:40,249 --> 00:00:42,542
It can't get any worse! But...

9
00:00:42,543 --> 00:00:44,669
Oh oh oh oh oh

10
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:46,921
Victory isn't about numbers

11
00:00:46,922 --> 00:00:49,215
Hi hi hi hi hi

12
00:00:49,216 --> 00:00:51,551
Show time
Let's turn it up!

13
00:00:51,552 --> 00:00:59,809
Overcome every trial
thrown at you by the heavens

14
00:00:59,810 --> 00:01:03,897
Raise the fist of fire!

15
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:06,692
Stand up and fight
That's what you call a hero!

16
00:01:06,984 --> 00:01:08,442
Anytime, anywhere

17
00:01:08,443 --> 00:01:13,239
Crush all the evil monsters that attack!

18
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:18,035
Come on, more (more), more (more)
I need the rush

19
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:22,457
This isn't enough
No satisfied yeah!

20
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:26,879
Just be stronger than anyone, anyone
Hey!

21
00:01:27,296 --> 00:01:31,341
Dance, dance across the sky
of destruction! Hey!

22
00:01:31,717 --> 00:01:36,013
Always, always finish it in one blow!

23
00:01:36,889 --> 00:01:40,392
One Punch!

24
00:01:41,018 --> 00:01:44,730
(Counterattack Signal)

25
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:25,938
What the...?

26
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,816
Why was I asleep?

27
00:02:30,359 --> 00:02:31,777
Ow... ow, ow, oww!

28
00:02:31,944 --> 00:02:34,821
Wait now.
What happened to me?

29
00:02:36,742 --> 00:02:39,578
I lost to a monster.

30
00:02:40,369 --> 00:02:41,912
Yet, I'm still alive.

31
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,121
What's going on?

32
00:02:44,957 --> 00:02:46,250
And what happened to that kid?

33
00:02:47,251 --> 00:02:50,712
That ugly brat.
Did they let him go?

34
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:52,464
Or don't tell me, they...

35
00:02:54,216 --> 00:02:55,425
It doesn't matter.

36
00:02:55,551 --> 00:02:57,261
I need to stop my bleeding.

37
00:02:57,469 --> 00:02:59,638
Actually... it's already stopped.

38
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:04,393
Hm? My clothes are stuck to the wounds
and won't come off.

39
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:06,520
They're completely fused together.

40
00:03:07,104 --> 00:03:08,355
Now then...

41
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:32,880
The signal from
Dig-Here Doggie No.3 broke off.

42
00:03:34,423 --> 00:03:36,842
He found it.
Which means we're close.

43
00:03:37,301 --> 00:03:39,052
I should be able to
pinpoint their base soon.

44
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:43,307
Are we finally zeroing in
on their stronghold, Child Emperor?

45
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,808
Mr. Sekingal.

46
00:03:45,559 --> 00:03:48,312
Tornado's been
pressuring us to hurry.

47
00:03:48,604 --> 00:03:50,439
Have the Class-S heroes gathered?

48
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:51,690
Not all of them.

49
00:03:52,274 --> 00:03:55,319
Tank-Top Master and Metal Bat
are in the hospital.

50
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:57,446
Drive Knight is missing.

51
00:03:57,613 --> 00:04:00,199
Watchdog Man and Metal Knight
have refused to participate.

52
00:04:00,324 --> 00:04:02,743
Not having everyone on board
this time really hurts.

53
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:05,120
Zombieman is on his way here.

54
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:07,706
We still haven't been able to
get in touch with...

55
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:11,335
Silverfang, Demon Cyborg, and King.

56
00:04:12,002 --> 00:04:14,254
We plan to add all three
to the team.

57
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:18,967
Class-S heroes are going to
be crucial to this operation.

58
00:04:19,801 --> 00:04:20,761
Wait a second.

59
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:25,933
Actually, I did a bit of research
on Genos the Demon Cyborg.

60
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:28,936
He lives in City Z's
ghost town, right?

61
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:32,314
The Monster Association's hideout is
somewhere in the ghost town, right?

62
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:36,360
Even the town he was born in
has disappeared from the map.

63
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,362
Doesn't that sound suspicious?

64
00:04:38,570 --> 00:04:42,156
There are lots of heroes with
unknown origins or secrets.

65
00:04:42,157 --> 00:04:43,367
Why mention this now?

66
00:04:43,742 --> 00:04:46,870
We still know very little about
the enemy organization.

67
00:04:47,329 --> 00:04:49,915
The number and strength
of the monsters remain unknown.

68
00:04:50,332 --> 00:04:52,124
If there's a traitor among us

69
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:55,379
our plans and infiltration routes
could be compromised.

70
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:57,506
We might all be wiped out
if things go wrong.

71
00:04:57,923 --> 00:05:01,927
Genos is a newcomer and hasn't
proven himself to gain our full trust.

72
00:05:02,469 --> 00:05:04,847
Don't trust anyone around you.

73
00:05:05,389 --> 00:05:07,933
Are you worried he might betray us?

74
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:10,936
If you have any doubts
just ask him directly.

75
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,938
No, we shouldn't
share any information with him

76
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:16,817
and he should be
entirely excluded from this operation.

77
00:05:18,527 --> 00:05:20,821
We can't afford
any more risk factors.

78
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:22,698
But from a strategic standpoint...

79
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:25,951
No, you're right.

80
00:05:26,410 --> 00:05:29,454
This is a rescue and sweep mission
we cannot afford to fail.

81
00:05:30,622 --> 00:05:33,333
Demon Cyborg is off the team.

82
00:05:34,084 --> 00:05:35,168
One more thing...

83
00:05:35,169 --> 00:05:38,630
I think it's odd that
Silverfang let Garou slip away.

84
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:42,467
He must have held back because of
his attachment to his former disciple.

85
00:05:43,969 --> 00:05:48,140
It's been confirmed that Garou is allied
with the Monster Association.

86
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:50,934
Unfortunately, we need to
remove Silverfang as well.

87
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,853
Understood.

88
00:05:55,022 --> 00:05:56,940
But you need King, right?

89
00:05:57,191 --> 00:05:58,274
Of course.

90
00:05:58,275 --> 00:06:00,360
King is one of our key fighters.

91
00:06:00,861 --> 00:06:05,032
The hideout should be located soon.
Let everyone know.

92
00:06:05,908 --> 00:06:09,536
You're removing Silverfang and
Demon Cyborg from the operation?

93
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:14,790
Yes. But instead, I'll gather
capable heroes from Class A to C

94
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,627
and have them support Class S.

95
00:06:17,252 --> 00:06:20,088
They may lack in combat ability,
but it's better than nothing.

96
00:06:20,506 --> 00:06:23,132
If they can support Class S even slightly
that's good enough.

97
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:25,177
Don't treat them like
they're disposable!

98
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:27,262
They could die!

99
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:30,933
I don't expect everyone who goes in
to make it out alive.

100
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:35,395
But that's a risk they accepted
when they chose the path of a pro hero.

101
00:06:35,771 --> 00:06:38,524
The life of a hostage is at stake.

102
00:06:38,774 --> 00:06:40,399
Some sacrifices are inevitable.

103
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:44,403
Sekingal... Have you thought
about the consequences?

104
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:48,699
If we lose more heroes to injury or death
we will be short-handed...

105
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,284
Sitch, I remember that you were

106
00:06:50,285 --> 00:06:53,080
in charge of the Earthdoom Prophecy
Emergency Response Team.

107
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:55,541
So I understand
where you're coming from.

108
00:06:56,083 --> 00:07:01,129
You want us to be prepared for a possible
worst-case scenario, right?

109
00:07:01,672 --> 00:07:04,257
But I have a different take on this.
(Earthdoom)

110
00:07:04,258 --> 00:07:04,715
(Earthdoom)

111
00:07:04,716 --> 00:07:06,467
The Monster Association itself is
(Earthdoom)

112
00:07:06,468 --> 00:07:08,803
what the "Earthdoom" prophecy was warning us about.
(Earthdoom)

113
00:07:08,804 --> 00:07:09,346
(Earthdoom)

114
00:07:09,555 --> 00:07:13,100
If left unchecked, they will
eventually destroy humanity.

115
00:07:13,559 --> 00:07:17,437
If that's the case, this is a
critical moment for the Hero Association.

116
00:07:17,855 --> 00:07:23,569
If we overcome this, we'll no longer live
in fear of that cursed prophecy.

117
00:07:23,986 --> 00:07:26,154
The future doesn't matter.

118
00:07:26,488 --> 00:07:30,325
In any case, I am the team leader
of the hostage rescue mission.

119
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:35,998
Don't contact Silverfang and the others
behind my back. Got that?

120
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:45,174
(Bubble Bubble)

121
00:07:47,092 --> 00:07:54,099
(Simmering)

122
00:08:07,238 --> 00:08:08,280
It's ready.

123
00:08:09,198 --> 00:08:10,240
(Swish)

124
00:08:10,532 --> 00:08:14,578
(Swish) (Swish) (Swish)

125
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:25,255
(Fwip)

126
00:08:28,425 --> 00:08:29,259
(Snatch)

127
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:33,804
Why are you taking Master's meat,
Hellish Blizzard?

128
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:35,766
Demon Cyborg Genos...

129
00:08:36,016 --> 00:08:38,852
Are you satisfied
being his sidekick?

130
00:08:39,093 --> 00:08:42,720
Stop it. Hot pots are meant to
be shared and enjoyed together.

131
00:08:42,721 --> 00:08:45,415
Hey, don't take all the tofu!

132
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:46,902
Hang on a sec.

133
00:08:47,611 --> 00:08:50,739
You know, there's
something that's bugging me.

134
00:08:51,823 --> 00:08:55,410
Why are you guys acting like it's totally
fine to eat someone else's hot pot?

135
00:08:56,286 --> 00:08:59,164
The napa cabbage is all gone.
Go home already.

136
00:08:59,289 --> 00:09:01,332
That's right.
Go home.

137
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,376
It's cramped in here.

138
00:09:02,501 --> 00:09:03,459
That includes you.

139
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:05,587
Silverfang I can understand.

140
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:09,466
But a random old man has no business
hanging out with this group.

141
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:13,553
If you want to join
the Blizzard Bunch

142
00:09:13,554 --> 00:09:16,181
you need to show me
you're worth it.

143
00:09:16,306 --> 00:09:17,223
(Sizzle)

144
00:09:17,224 --> 00:09:19,267
Huh? The Blizzard Bunch?
(Sizzle)

145
00:09:19,268 --> 00:09:19,517
(Sizzle)

146
00:09:19,518 --> 00:09:22,070
You want me to annihilate you?

147
00:09:22,071 --> 00:09:24,348
Wait, Genos!
Don't break anything!

148
00:09:24,581 --> 00:09:26,290
Calm down, Genos.

149
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:28,443
- This isn't like you.
- Right.

150
00:09:28,610 --> 00:09:33,030
I feel as though I've gotten to see
a new side of you.

151
00:09:33,031 --> 00:09:34,783
That makes me happy.

152
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:39,037
You can forget about fighting,
share a hot pot, and speak openly here.

153
00:09:39,162 --> 00:09:41,372
You're lucky to have
good friends, Genos.

154
00:09:41,373 --> 00:09:42,457
Doctor...

155
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:44,917
This woman is not my friend.

156
00:09:44,918 --> 00:09:46,627
"This woman"?
How rude.

157
00:09:46,628 --> 00:09:48,171
R-Really?

158
00:09:48,172 --> 00:09:50,632
But you're both heroes from
the same organization, right?

159
00:09:50,841 --> 00:09:53,051
Yes, but that's totally irrelevant.

160
00:09:53,385 --> 00:09:54,218
I see.

161
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:58,556
Wow... He's never disagreed with me
so adamantly.

162
00:09:58,557 --> 00:10:00,808
I just saw another side of him.

163
00:10:00,809 --> 00:10:03,103
You said your name
is Kuseno, right?

164
00:10:03,687 --> 00:10:08,108
You've got impressive skills
crafting weapons for Demon Cyborg.

165
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:12,236
We could hire you to develop weapons
for the Blizzard Bunch.

166
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:17,409
Hey... If you insult Dr. Kuseno
any more, I'll incinerate you.

167
00:10:17,618 --> 00:10:20,120
Now, now. It's quite all right.

168
00:10:20,412 --> 00:10:21,663
Saitama.

169
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:26,167
I wanted to ask you about
your thoughts on how to train disciples.

170
00:10:26,168 --> 00:10:29,588
Huh? My thoughts?
I don't really have any in particular.

171
00:10:29,838 --> 00:10:32,508
Where did I go wrong?

172
00:10:32,925 --> 00:10:35,635
Our dojo valued strength
more than anything else.

173
00:10:35,636 --> 00:10:37,596
Maybe that was wrong?

174
00:10:37,846 --> 00:10:39,014
Depends on the person.

175
00:10:39,223 --> 00:10:44,895
Hey Bang, don't start a long story
while Master Saitama is eating.

176
00:10:45,854 --> 00:10:47,022
Hey, Bang's brother.

177
00:10:47,481 --> 00:10:49,733
Stop hoarding the napa cabbage
and give some to Master.

178
00:10:53,128 --> 00:10:56,047
Hey, Kuseno.
Can you pass me the tea?

179
00:10:56,048 --> 00:10:58,951
Hey, don't tell the doctor
what to do.

180
00:11:02,262 --> 00:11:06,098
Kuseno, old man. Could you bring
some good meat next time, too?

181
00:11:06,099 --> 00:11:08,126
Stop making rude requests...

182
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:10,170
I'm so sorry, Master!

183
00:11:11,213 --> 00:11:12,965
You should rest, Genos.

184
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:22,516
Hard to relax with
so many people here.

185
00:11:22,683 --> 00:11:24,810
Once you're done eating
just go home, seriously.

186
00:11:25,136 --> 00:11:26,095
You too, King.

187
00:11:26,697 --> 00:11:28,741
Huh? How come you're lying down?

188
00:11:29,189 --> 00:11:30,816
Hey, don't fall asleep here!

189
00:11:31,066 --> 00:11:33,193
Hey, hey!

190
00:11:35,654 --> 00:11:36,655
He's dead.

191
00:12:06,143 --> 00:12:09,396
An intruder...
In passage A-8...

192
00:12:09,938 --> 00:12:11,648
It's not a machine.
It's a living being.

193
00:12:12,024 --> 00:12:13,984
A monster who wants to join us?

194
00:12:14,318 --> 00:12:16,653
Or perhaps a scout from
the Hero Association?

195
00:12:17,196 --> 00:12:19,489
No, but to come here all alone...

196
00:12:19,907 --> 00:12:22,159
That's far too reckless.

197
00:12:22,701 --> 00:12:26,747
The final battle is approaching,
so I must verify this carefully.

198
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:28,122
Listen up.

199
00:12:28,123 --> 00:12:31,251
Looks like something's here again.
Go greet it.

200
00:12:31,543 --> 00:12:33,712
If it's a monster, bring it here.

201
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:36,965
If it's anything else,
do whatever you want with them.

202
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:45,432
Hey, wake up already!
It's morning.

203
00:12:46,350 --> 00:12:47,309
Hey!

204
00:12:48,769 --> 00:12:51,480
Hm? What am I doing here?

205
00:12:51,605 --> 00:12:53,690
You passed out fighting over meat.

206
00:12:54,066 --> 00:12:55,317
I thought you were a goner.

207
00:12:57,361 --> 00:12:58,654
Where are the others?

208
00:12:59,071 --> 00:13:00,864
I kicked them out after dinner.

209
00:13:01,365 --> 00:13:02,407
Genos is getting repairs.

210
00:13:02,699 --> 00:13:05,535
I-I see. I'm the only one
who stayed over?

211
00:13:05,536 --> 00:13:07,704
Sorry, Saitama.

212
00:13:08,247 --> 00:13:09,248
Don't worry about it.

213
00:13:09,706 --> 00:13:12,125
On your way out,
take the trash to the dump.

214
00:13:12,626 --> 00:13:15,504
It's in the residential area,
so it's kinda far from here.

215
00:13:16,755 --> 00:13:18,590
They're collecting
plastic bottles today.

216
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:22,886
Wow, I slept really well.

217
00:13:23,637 --> 00:13:25,847
What a peaceful
and refreshing morning

218
00:13:25,848 --> 00:13:28,141
with no noise from people or cars.

219
00:13:29,059 --> 00:13:30,435
A ghost town...

220
00:13:30,853 --> 00:13:35,023
They say the high monster
appearance rate drove people away

221
00:13:35,357 --> 00:13:37,651
but surprisingly,
I haven't run into any at all.

222
00:13:38,402 --> 00:13:43,323
Maybe Saitama living here actually
drove the monsters away.

223
00:13:44,283 --> 00:13:46,909
They say if you keep a cat in
a house infested with rats

224
00:13:46,910 --> 00:13:48,996
the rats will disappear.

225
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:53,250
But... sometimes the rats are
just hiding in the attic.

226
00:13:53,584 --> 00:13:57,379
Maybe monsters are gathering
underground in nests instead...

227
00:13:58,589 --> 00:14:01,842
Yuck... Just thinking about it
gives me the creeps.

228
00:14:05,352 --> 00:14:06,979
Hm? Hey, did you just...

229
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:09,765
...come from
the other side of the fence?

230
00:14:09,766 --> 00:14:11,560
No, you must be imagining things!

231
00:14:13,729 --> 00:14:15,272
There, all done.

232
00:14:17,024 --> 00:14:20,402
It's amazing that people still go to work
even in times like this.

233
00:14:25,991 --> 00:14:28,660
Hm?
Someone's in front of my house.

234
00:14:29,328 --> 00:14:31,205
Oh! He's home!

235
00:14:31,955 --> 00:14:35,250
Thank god.
We've been waiting for you, King!

236
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:38,587
We couldn't get in touch with you,
so we searched everywhere!

237
00:14:38,754 --> 00:14:40,339
Oh, they're from the Association.

238
00:14:40,506 --> 00:14:45,594
Oh, sorry.
My transmitter was broken during a fight.

239
00:14:45,802 --> 00:14:47,304
Where were you last night?

240
00:14:47,471 --> 00:14:49,264
Umm, City Z.

241
00:14:50,182 --> 00:14:51,600
Those stains on your clothes!

242
00:14:51,767 --> 00:14:53,935
Bodily fluids and flesh
from monsters?

243
00:14:53,936 --> 00:14:56,103
- This is from the hot pot...
- You must've been in

244
00:14:56,104 --> 00:14:58,649
- Did I have any?
- An intense battle all night long.

245
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:04,487
King, you must be exhausted
having fought without sleep or rest

246
00:15:04,488 --> 00:15:07,407
but we need you to accompany us
to the Headquarters at once!

247
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:19,126
Captain Tongara said
he'd contact me every two hours

248
00:15:19,127 --> 00:15:22,506
but I haven't heard anything
from the unit all night.

249
00:15:23,048 --> 00:15:25,091
I assembled the best possible team

250
00:15:25,092 --> 00:15:27,135
and equipped them with
the finest weapons.

251
00:15:27,511 --> 00:15:28,846
Did the operation fail?

252
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:30,347
Were they wiped out?

253
00:15:30,722 --> 00:15:33,225
Could they really be
defeated so easily?

254
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:37,521
Even if the heroes head there,
won't they meet the same fate?

255
00:15:38,814 --> 00:15:39,773
Mr. Narinki.

256
00:15:41,275 --> 00:15:42,860
Looks like
you haven't slept all night.

257
00:15:43,485 --> 00:15:45,612
Why don't you go lie down
in the break room?

258
00:15:46,154 --> 00:15:50,826
Sekingal, my elite unit may
have been wiped out.

259
00:15:51,326 --> 00:15:52,369
This is terrifying.

260
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:54,121
I have a bad feeling about this.

261
00:15:54,538 --> 00:15:56,999
At this rate,
we'll be crushed completely.

262
00:15:57,291 --> 00:15:58,292
Don't worry.

263
00:15:58,834 --> 00:16:02,546
I've told you before that
we will rescue your son.

264
00:16:03,046 --> 00:16:05,257
Please trust the Hero Association.

265
00:16:05,591 --> 00:16:07,634
Do we really have
a chance of winning?

266
00:16:08,135 --> 00:16:11,471
Metal Bat was defeated
even though he is a Class-S hero.

267
00:16:11,805 --> 00:16:13,807
I have no reason to trust you.

268
00:16:13,932 --> 00:16:16,685
You're not just putting on
a brave front, are you?

269
00:16:17,436 --> 00:16:19,478
Please... my son...

270
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:22,316
You're his only hope.

271
00:16:22,858 --> 00:16:25,319
I'll give you as much
money as you want.

272
00:16:25,569 --> 00:16:29,198
Please! I just want to
see Waganma alive and well.

273
00:16:29,448 --> 00:16:30,991
For my son...!

274
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,703
I'll give everything I own
to the Hero Association!!

275
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:35,913
That won't be necessary.

276
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:37,581
Who said that?

277
00:16:37,956 --> 00:16:41,585
Only those weaker than money
are swayed by it.

278
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:46,089
People like that are useless
in a battle against monsters.

279
00:16:46,256 --> 00:16:47,257
Exactly!

280
00:16:47,799 --> 00:16:51,637
What's needed on the battlefield
is true courage to face evil.

281
00:16:52,012 --> 00:16:54,515
Isn't that what you're
trying to say, Flashy Flash?

282
00:16:54,723 --> 00:16:57,935
You're wrong.
Mindset is secondary.

283
00:16:58,185 --> 00:16:59,978
All that matters is strength.

284
00:17:00,103 --> 00:17:01,939
So just leave everything to me.

285
00:17:02,231 --> 00:17:06,652
Protecting the child is the top priority.
That's why we must act as a team.

286
00:17:06,985 --> 00:17:09,278
If it were just a matter of
taking them down like usual

287
00:17:09,279 --> 00:17:11,406
I'd have charged in with
my disciples long ago.

288
00:17:11,532 --> 00:17:14,201
Storming the monster hideout
with this team...

289
00:17:14,493 --> 00:17:16,078
Simple and straightforward.
I like it.

290
00:17:16,578 --> 00:17:19,790
I've been wanting to smash
an organization like this.

291
00:17:19,915 --> 00:17:24,419
I'll give everything I've got to bring
back that boy and my beloved inmates!

292
00:17:24,878 --> 00:17:27,089
I swear it on
this hand-knit sweater!

293
00:17:27,798 --> 00:17:29,591
I've located their hideout.

294
00:17:29,883 --> 00:17:32,010
All we need is King
and the backup team.

295
00:17:32,886 --> 00:17:33,386
We go in at noon.

296
00:17:33,387 --> 00:17:34,220
(The Class-S Heroes Are Here!!)
We go in at noon.

297
00:17:34,221 --> 00:17:34,846
(The Class-S Heroes Are Here!!)

298
00:17:34,847 --> 00:17:37,765
We'll rescue the boy and
defeat the Monster Association.

299
00:17:37,766 --> 00:17:38,766
(The Class-S Heroes Are Here!!)

300
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:40,560
Don't worry about a thing
and get some sleep.

301
00:17:40,561 --> 00:17:43,313
By the time you wake up,
it'll all be over, old man.

302
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,438
Hey now!

303
00:17:44,439 --> 00:17:47,192
Mr. Narinki is the Hero Association's
top advisor, you know!

304
00:17:47,568 --> 00:17:50,946
The Class-S heroes are going to have
a brief strategy meeting, right?

305
00:17:51,196 --> 00:17:52,322
Let's get going.

306
00:17:52,447 --> 00:17:54,616
I think I'll go lie down a bit...

307
00:17:54,825 --> 00:17:56,994
I'm leaving it all to you,
Sekingal.

308
00:17:57,202 --> 00:17:58,245
Yes, you can count on me!

309
00:17:59,538 --> 00:18:02,165
I'll give each of you
a map of the ghost town.

310
00:18:02,541 --> 00:18:04,917
I've confirmed
multiple entry points

311
00:18:04,918 --> 00:18:07,504
so we'll split up
and enter simultaneously.

312
00:18:07,921 --> 00:18:09,840
I'll explain route assignments now.

313
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:12,885
We finally gathered everyone,
but we're gonna split up to fight?

314
00:18:13,093 --> 00:18:15,387
The monsters are doing the same.

315
00:18:15,512 --> 00:18:17,639
Staying in one group
risks total wipeout.

316
00:18:18,015 --> 00:18:20,851
I'll give each of you a transmitter
to track our positions.

317
00:18:23,312 --> 00:18:25,313
We need to prioritize
the hostage's safety

318
00:18:25,314 --> 00:18:26,940
so we need a
short, decisive battle.

319
00:18:27,107 --> 00:18:29,985
As long as even one of us
reaches the hostage, that's enough.

320
00:18:30,611 --> 00:18:32,988
The backup members will
wait aboveground.

321
00:18:33,405 --> 00:18:35,448
If any monsters try to escape
from underground

322
00:18:35,449 --> 00:18:36,909
they'll be there
to finish them off.

323
00:18:37,159 --> 00:18:40,120
Oh, like the Whack-A-Mole game.

324
00:18:40,287 --> 00:18:42,455
We can't have
a bunch of monsters

325
00:18:42,456 --> 00:18:44,374
spilling into
the residential areas again.

326
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:46,251
About the backup members...

327
00:18:46,668 --> 00:18:49,379
We've been recruiting every
reasonably capable fighter available.

328
00:18:49,671 --> 00:18:51,422
They should be able to
handle monsters

329
00:18:51,423 --> 00:18:53,217
up to threat-level Tiger
without issue.

330
00:18:53,342 --> 00:18:55,385
Don't tell me you called Blizzard.

331
00:18:55,511 --> 00:18:58,722
Hm? Oh yeah,
I did reach out to her.

332
00:18:59,056 --> 00:19:01,183
Hellish Blizzard
is a valuable asset.

333
00:19:01,517 --> 00:19:03,309
She's already on her way here.

334
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:08,065
Absolutely not. Don't put
my little sister in danger.

335
00:19:08,565 --> 00:19:11,401
If you drag her into this battle
I won't forgive you.

336
00:19:11,693 --> 00:19:14,320
With me here,
that's more than enough. Got it?

337
00:19:14,321 --> 00:19:16,365
- But...
- What is your answer?

338
00:19:16,657 --> 00:19:18,951
Uh, understood.

339
00:19:19,201 --> 00:19:21,954
I'll call her
and tell her to stand down.

340
00:19:28,335 --> 00:19:29,378
Good morning.

341
00:19:30,045 --> 00:19:33,131
Have you been behaving?
I've come to get you.

342
00:19:33,423 --> 00:19:35,925
Just Tareo can step outside.
Let's go.

343
00:19:35,926 --> 00:19:38,678
What?! Why is he
the only one getting released?

344
00:19:38,679 --> 00:19:39,595
Not fair!

345
00:19:39,596 --> 00:19:42,181
Released? No, no.

346
00:19:42,182 --> 00:19:46,395
He's coming to my room.
So we can play.

347
00:19:47,162 --> 00:19:49,080
Well, you heard him.
You'd better go.

348
00:19:49,081 --> 00:19:52,609
N-No way!
I don't wanna! Help!

349
00:19:52,776 --> 00:19:56,279
Heroes! Hurry up
and save me, heroes!

350
00:19:56,280 --> 00:20:00,075
Um, I hate to tell you, but...

351
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:04,371
The Hero Association is only trying
to rescue that kid over there.

352
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:06,874
No one even knows you're here.

353
00:20:07,249 --> 00:20:10,210
No hero is ever coming to save you.

354
00:20:14,548 --> 00:20:19,803
Apparently, the monsters who went to
check on the intruder never came back.

355
00:20:20,053 --> 00:20:23,432
If they were killed then that means
the heroes have arrived?

356
00:20:23,891 --> 00:20:26,226
But we haven't heard any signal
to start the fight yet.

357
00:20:26,351 --> 00:20:29,061
According to Gyoro-Gyoro,
there's only one intruder.

358
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:31,607
They're probably not affiliated
with the Hero Association.

359
00:20:33,734 --> 00:20:35,027
Look at this mess.

360
00:20:35,152 --> 00:20:38,363
Maybe that thing isn't even human,
after all.

361
00:20:38,822 --> 00:20:41,116
So that means the intruder
is a monster?

362
00:20:41,742 --> 00:20:46,079
Yeah, it could've been a
hot-tempered monster like King the Ripper.

363
00:20:46,246 --> 00:20:50,751
There are plenty of monsters out there
who hate the Monster Association.

364
00:20:51,143 --> 00:20:53,311
It'll be a pain
if things got chaotic

365
00:20:53,312 --> 00:20:55,547
before the showdown with
the Class-S heroes.

366
00:20:55,714 --> 00:20:59,801
Either way, just like Gyoro-Gyoro said
we need to deal with them pronto.

367
00:21:00,344 --> 00:21:03,138
By the way, where is King the Ripper?

368
00:21:03,305 --> 00:21:06,849
This is the perfect time for
a bloodthirsty psycho.

369
00:21:06,850 --> 00:21:08,392
Well, if he's not here

370
00:21:08,393 --> 00:21:10,521
then he's with the kid
he snatched yesterday.

371
00:21:10,646 --> 00:21:13,524
He probably can't hold
himself back anymore.

372
00:21:15,429 --> 00:21:18,681
Stop!

373
00:21:18,682 --> 00:21:21,573
Someone... Help me!

374
00:21:24,535 --> 00:21:26,745
Such a cute reaction.

375
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:29,872
Why? Why are you doing this?

376
00:21:29,873 --> 00:21:33,085
Why? Because I'm a monster.

377
00:21:33,377 --> 00:21:37,631
Honestly, I couldn't care less
about this big war of theirs.

378
00:21:37,881 --> 00:21:42,052
I don't really need a new world
ruled by monsters.

379
00:21:42,261 --> 00:21:44,470
As long as I can unleash
my urge to shred flesh

380
00:21:44,471 --> 00:21:45,513
that's all I need.

381
00:21:45,514 --> 00:21:46,765
Stop...

382
00:21:47,015 --> 00:21:49,392
Killing is my only reason
for living.

383
00:21:49,393 --> 00:21:51,311
And right now,
I'm obsessed with you.

384
00:21:51,436 --> 00:21:52,728
H-Help!

385
00:21:52,729 --> 00:21:54,606
First, your tongue.

386
00:21:54,731 --> 00:21:58,068
Help... me!!

387
00:22:01,071 --> 00:22:02,030
It's...

388
00:22:05,284 --> 00:22:06,285
You!!

389
00:22:19,756 --> 00:22:21,091
Old dude!

390
00:22:22,009 --> 00:22:24,094
Come on, let's go, you little brat.

391
00:22:46,366 --> 00:22:56,334
Floating in the same moment
at the edge of righteousness

392
00:22:56,335 --> 00:23:06,052
If your feelings are wandering alone

393
00:23:06,053 --> 00:23:12,851
I'll greet them
with the same familiar face

394
00:23:14,061 --> 00:23:19,023
If the light that shines there

395
00:23:19,024 --> 00:23:26,322
Illuminates all of us equally now

396
00:23:26,323 --> 00:23:36,207
Embrace the pain and solitude
just as they are

397
00:23:36,208 --> 00:23:44,675
With a wish burning in my heart,
I'll press forward

398
00:23:56,019 --> 00:24:00,899
(Monster King)

